<subSubSection pageId="93" pageNumber="94" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="93.[151,1437,751,958]" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,787,813]" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kluge, Godunko &amp; Svitok" authorityYear="2020" box="[342,555,787,813]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Centroptella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifida">
<emphasis box="[342,555,787,813]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Centroptella bifida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known as larvae only. According to the original description, its larvae differ from others as «submarginal setae on labrum are forked apically» (
<bibRefCitation author="Shi, W &amp; Tong, X." box="[911,1169,823,850]" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" pagination="571 - 585" refId="ref65409" refString="Shi, W, &amp; Tong, X. (2019) Genus Bungona Harker, 1957 (Ephemeroptera: Baetidae) from China, with descriptions of three new species and a key to Oriental species. Zootaxa, 4586 (3), 571 - 585. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4586.3.12" type="journal article" year="2019">Shi &amp; Tong 2019: 578</bibRefCitation>
, 584, fig. 37). Actually, these setae are bifurcate in some other species as well, particularly in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kluge, Godunko &amp; Svitok" authorityYear="2020" box="[915,1041,859,886]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Centroptella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ingridae">
<emphasis box="[915,1041,859,886]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">C. ingridae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1055,1151,859,886]" captionStart="FIGURES 395–398" captionStartId="86.[151,264,1808,1832]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,381,1780]" captionTargetId="figure-91@86.[158,1430,381,1785]" captionTargetPageId="86" captionText="FIGURES 395–398. Centroptella (Crassolus) ingridae, larva. 395, labrum (SEM picture by R. Godunko); 396–397, left and right mandibles; 398, male abdominal terga with reddish and orange hypodermal coloration visible through cuticle." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5577554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5577554/files/figure.png" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Fig. 395</figureCitation>
), which in the same paper by 
<bibRefCitation author="Shi, W &amp; Tong, X." box="[185,393,895,922]" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" pagination="571 - 585" refId="ref65409" refString="Shi, W, &amp; Tong, X. (2019) Genus Bungona Harker, 1957 (Ephemeroptera: Baetidae) from China, with descriptions of three new species and a key to Oriental species. Zootaxa, 4586 (3), 571 - 585. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4586.3.12" type="journal article" year="2019">Shi &amp; Tong (2019)</bibRefCitation>
was redescribed under the name « 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Salles, Gattolliat &amp; Sartori" authorityYear="2015" box="[772,1142,895,922]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Bungona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="liebenauae" subGenus="Chopralla">
<emphasis box="[772,873,896,921]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Bungona</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[888,1003,895,921]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Chopralla</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1019,1142,895,921]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">liebenauae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
» and told to have «labrum surface with simple submarginal setae» (
<bibRefCitation author="Shi, W &amp; Tong, X." box="[607,862,931,958]" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" pagination="571 - 585" refId="ref65409" refString="Shi, W, &amp; Tong, X. (2019) Genus Bungona Harker, 1957 (Ephemeroptera: Baetidae) from China, with descriptions of three new species and a key to Oriental species. Zootaxa, 4586 (3), 571 - 585. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4586.3.12" type="journal article" year="2019">Shi &amp; Tong 2019: 584</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5577568" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5577568" box="[151,1078,1650,1674]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5577568/files/figure.png" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" startId="93.[151,250,1650,1674]" targetBox="[346,1242,982,1626]" targetPageId="93">
<paragraph blockId="93.[151,1078,1650,1674]" box="[151,1078,1650,1674]" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,301,1650,1674]" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">FIGURE 421.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kluge, Godunko &amp; Svitok" authorityYear="2020" box="[307,434,1650,1674]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Centroptella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[307,434,1650,1674]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Centroptella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[449,550,1650,1674]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Crassolus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[449,550,1650,1674]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Crassolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
?) 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kluge, Godunko &amp; Svitok" authorityYear="2020" box="[576,635,1650,1674]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Centroptella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifida">
<emphasis box="[576,635,1650,1674]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">bifida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, mature male larva (photo by Xiaoli Tong).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="93.[151,1437,1720,2035]" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">
Form of right prostheca (pressed to kinetodontium and lacking long process) suggests that 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kluge, Godunko &amp; Svitok" authorityYear="2020" box="[1240,1340,1720,1746]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Centroptella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifida">
<emphasis box="[1240,1340,1720,1746]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">C. bifida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs either to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Waltz &amp; McCafferty" authorityYear="1987" box="[253,368,1756,1782]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Chopralla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[253,368,1756,1782]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Chopralla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, or to 
<taxonomicName box="[444,556,1756,1782]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Crassolus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[444,556,1756,1782]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Crassolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Male larvae used for the original description, are not mature enough to have subimaginal gonostyli, so their pose is unknown (Xiaoli Tong, personal communication). Judging by the presence of denticles on posterior margins of abdominal terga II–X and the presence of setal rows (j) on abdominal sterna III–VI (
<bibRefCitation author="Shi, W &amp; Tong, X." box="[159,414,1864,1891]" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" pagination="571 - 585" refId="ref65409" refString="Shi, W, &amp; Tong, X. (2019) Genus Bungona Harker, 1957 (Ephemeroptera: Baetidae) from China, with descriptions of three new species and a key to Oriental species. Zootaxa, 4586 (3), 571 - 585. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4586.3.12" type="journal article" year="2019">Shi &amp; Tong 2019: 578</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kluge, Godunko &amp; Svitok" authorityYear="2020" box="[433,531,1864,1890]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Centroptella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifida">
<emphasis box="[433,531,1864,1890]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">C. bifida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
probably belongs to 
<taxonomicName box="[768,880,1864,1890]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Crassolus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[768,880,1864,1890]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Crassolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="93.[151,1437,1720,2035]" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">
Judging by the picture provided by Xiaoli Tong (
<figureCitation box="[746,843,1900,1926]" captionStart="FIGURE 421" captionStartId="93.[151,250,1650,1674]" captionTargetBox="[346,1242,982,1626]" captionTargetId="figure-265@93.[346,1242,982,1626]" captionTargetPageId="93" captionText="FIGURE 421. Centroptella (Crassolus?) bifida, mature male larva (photo by Xiaoli Tong)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5577568" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5577568/files/figure.png" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Fig. 421</figureCitation>
), hypodermal coloration of mature male larva is limited by reddish stripes on posterior margins of abdominal terga, that clearly separates this species from such representatives of 
<taxonomicName box="[297,409,1972,1998]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Crassolus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[297,409,1972,1998]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Crassolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kluge" authorityYear="2021" box="[452,582,1972,1998]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Centroptella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ludmilae">
<emphasis box="[452,582,1972,1998]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">C. ludmilae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kluge, Godunko &amp; Svitok" authorityYear="2020" box="[595,711,1972,1998]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Centroptella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pontica">
<emphasis box="[595,711,1972,1998]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">C. pontica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Crass" baseAuthorityYear="1947" box="[725,851,1972,1998]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Centroptella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inzingae">
<emphasis box="[725,851,1972,1998]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">C. inzingae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kluge, Godunko &amp; Svitok" authorityYear="2020" box="[904,1045,1972,1998]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Centroptella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saxophila">
<emphasis box="[904,1045,1972,1998]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">C. saxophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whose males have more extensive hypodermal coloration on abdominal terga.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
